Overview | Bel Air Investment Advisors


























 









Pershing Access
Client Login
  
 
 












Select Page


  
 



 



 












 
 
 
 
 
 




DistinctionAdvantageHistorySocial Commitment



An industry leader in providing customized managed services and investment counsel exclusively to high net worth individuals, families and foundations with $20 million or more in investable assets, Bel Air Investment Advisors LLC (Bel Air) distinguishes itself through its diverse mix of “best-in-class” proprietary and sub-advisory investment strategies, within its open architecture platform.
It further distinguishes itself by its very size — big enough to have formed solid relationships with leading globally-focused asset managers while small enough to tenaciously adhere to a single-minded and personalized approach to investing that provides accessibility, at all times, to decision makers of a client’s portfolio.
The firm’s leading Investment advisors, some with over 35 years of investment experience who oversee and manage approximately $7 billion in assets, have navigated industry fluctuations and diverse market conditions. They have repeatedly demonstrated their ability to cater to specific client needs and preferences, in virtually every situation.
Bel Air advisors’ keen understanding, objectivity, comprehensive knowledge and integrated experience in the market, are key in identifying and selecting the most appropriate investment options for each of their clients’ and in protecting and preserving their wealth.
Bel Air upholds the highest standards of professionalism and integrity and achieves excellence through strong management practices, sound business principles and the highest level of ethical behavior.
 
Clients face complex financial decisions — whether selling a business or other substantial asset, taking a company public, inheriting a large sum of capital, experiencing a divorce situation, or bearing responsibilities for investing foundation assets. Clients value the relationship with highly experienced investment advisors who have helped solve every critical investment challenge with a customized approach to addressing specific financial needs.
Bel Air’s advisors stay at the forefront of the industry landscape, continuously assessing industry trends, legislative forces and market shifts. They are focused on seeking out creative means to unlock potential opportunities and negotiate challenges on a client’s behalf.
Of particular note, are the firm’s market and technical sophistication, as well as its investment expertise, which reflects an astute understanding of, and sensitivity to, clients’ risk/reward preferences. Clients trust the firm’s advisors to guide them in managing the responsibilities and challenges inherent in protecting their wealth, and hold that guidance in high esteem.
As part of its private client service offering, the firm leverages its numerous relationships with asset managers, both domestically and internationally focused, who complement Bel Air’s financial knowledge and proprietary investment strategies. This affords clients the widest selection and the most appropriate investment options.
Its open architecture and private ownership structure enables Bel Air Investment Advisors to align clients’ interests with market opportunities, delivering top-tier investment strategies and strong long-term returns.
 
Bel Air’s founders Todd Morgan, Reed Halladay and Darell Krasnoff are widely respected in the investment community. While at Goldman Sachs & Co the three were leaders in Wall Street’s transition from brokerage to discretionary fee-based client services. Since founding Bel Air over a decade ago, the Firm has added significant professional talent and continues to use their expertise in the delivery of Bel Air’s premier client service model.
Bel Air was founded in 1997 as a wealth management firm.
 
Bel Air believes in corporate social responsibility within the community in which it does business and, as such, takes part in many philanthropic activities as a company. Bel Air’s philanthropic program supports employees’ selection of their own organizations and nonprofits, through the offering of an annual match donation for each employee to give to a charitable organization of their choice. Moreover, the firm encourages employees to participate in charitable activities of their choosing, by giving them paid time off for that purpose.
Bel Air regularly supports local organizations through hands-on, group community projects in addition to financial support. Bel Air has supported numerous foundations and organizations through Board membership, donations, and volunteering. Examples include but are not limited to the Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, Los Angeles County Museum of Art, Los Angeles Music Center, City of Hope, Pasadena Museum of California Art, Museum of Contemporary Art, Los Angeles, and more.
 
 
 
 

